Magic weaponry is generally split between regular spellcasting and [[powered staff|powered staves]] (often called "tridents"). For regular spellcasting, the [[Kodai wand]] is the strongest option, followed by the [[Master wand]] and [[Staff of the dead]]. At lower levels, the [[ancient staff]] is useful for casting [[Ancient Magick]]s, and [[elemental staves]] can be useful for saving runes when casting. For powered staves, the [[Sanguinesti staff]] is the strongest option, followed by the [[Trident of the swamp]] and the [[Trident of the sea]] (which is notably easier to maintain in terms of charges). The [[Iban's staff]] and [[Iban's staff (u)|its upgraded version]] are viable staves at lower levels, before better weapons are available.

The strongest Magic armour is the [[Ancestral robes]] set, followed by [[Ahrim the Blighted's equipment]] and [[Mystic robes]]. Mystic robes can be bought as needed from the [[Magic Guild Store (Mystic Robes)|Magic Guild Store]], which can save inventory space. The [[Farseer helm]] and [[Healer hat]] are both strong Magic helmet options, being buyable and storeable, respectively.

The best Magic off-hand item is the [[arcane spirit shield]], however it is very a difficult and time-consuming item to obtain. followed by the [[book of darkness]] and [[unholy book]] are both weaker. These books can be easily retrieved from [[Perdu]], making them an excellent off-hand option at all levels. The [[tome of fire]] is also a good low-level option, particularly for [[fire spells]] where its special effect is useful.

The [[imbued god cape]]s are the strongest Magic capes to use due to their Magic damage bonus, and they can be easily stored on the player's [[cape rack]]. At low levels, regular [[god cape]]s or [[Ardougne cloak]]s can be used instead for some Magic accuracy.

The [[tormented bracelet]] is the best option for the hand slot. Its Magic damage bonus makes it substantially better than any other handwear, making it very useful for any scenarios where Magic is used, such as Slayer training, Zulrah, Barrows, and Chambers of Xeric. If the player does not have the tormented bracelet, the best [[culinaromancer's gloves]] available can be used for some Magic accuracy.

For Magic boots, the [[wizard boots]] are the generally the best option as they can be stored in the player's [[treasure chest]]. If the player does not have the wizard boots, [[mystic boots]] can be dropped and easily re-bought as needed. While the [[eternal boots]] offer a higher Magic attack bonus, they bring very little benefit to most combat situations and therefore most players consider them not worth keeping.

The [[occult necklace]] is the strongest Magic neckwear available. Its Magic damage bonus makes it substantially better than any other neckwear, making it very useful for any scenarios where Magic is used, such as Slayer training, Zulrah, Barrows, and raids. If the player does not have the occult necklace, [[amulet of fury]] or [[amulet of glory]] can be used for some Magic accuracy.

For the ring slot, the [[brimstone ring]] is the generally the best option as it also provides bonuses for other combat styles. While the [[seers ring (i)]] offers a higher Magic attack bonus, magic rings are seldomly used, so most players consider the seers ring not worth keeping. Additionally, the seers ring cannot be stored in the looting bag while imbued (it can be unimbued for an 80% points refund at the [[Nightmare Zone]]).

