{{Main|Chambers of Xeric/Strategies}}
The Chambers of Xeric is a '''safe''' activity, which means players can store their items at an Item Retrieval Service for extra space. Players should bring the looting bag to store the valuable loot obtained from raiding. Having a fast method to get back to Mount Quidamortem is recommended, as this saves time in between raids. Players should bring the rune pouch with Teleport to House runes inside, or the Construction cape.

In order to save inventory space, [[Void Knight equipment]] is a popular equipment choice, as it allows for switching between Melee, Magic, and Ranged without having to bring alternate armours and gloves. This extra space makes up for the noted potions most Ultimate Ironman players will have in their inventory, and allow for more weapon, amulet, and cape switches. More experienced raiders can bring dedicated high-level equipment (such as [[Armadyl armour]] or [[Ancestral robes]]) if they feel comfortable doing the raid with fewer supplies.

For the main melee weapon, having the [[dragon hunter lance]] is strongly recommended as it is one of the best weapons to use against the Great Olm. Players who do not have the dragon hunter lance can alternatively use the Ghrazi rapier or the Blade of Saeldor instead. At the very minimum, players should have at least the abyssal whip or the zamorakian hasta. 

Players should bring a relatively small amount of noted potions into the raid, so they can be dropped before the Great Olm for extra inventory spaces for potions made inside the raid. Items dropped inside the raid will stay on the ground for 30 minutes, but they will be lost should the player leave the raid. Therefore, players should only bring the amount of noted potions they do not mind potentially losing.
