{{Main|Theatre of Blood/Strategies}}
The [[Theatre of Blood]] is a '''dangerous''' activity, which means players are strongly advised not to store their items at an Item Retrieval Service, as it is likely to die to mistakes or a disconnection. It is recommended to have a lot of looting bag space, so players can store all their items and valuable loot obtained from the Theatre.

The [[Void Knight equipment]] is the best equipment choice, as it allows for switching between Melee, Magic, and Ranged without having to bring alternate armours and gloves. This extra space makes up for the noted potions most Ultimate Ironman players will have in their inventory, and allow for more weapon, amulet, and cape switches.

For the main Melee weapon, the [[blade of Saeldor (c)]] is the best option for most players, as the [[scythe of vitur]] is only obtainable from the Theatre. The [[abyssal tentacle]] is the second best option, but because maintaining charges for the abyssal tentacle can be inconvenient, many players opt to use the [[abyssal whip]] instead.

Players should bring two [[special attack]] weapons: one for defence reduction and one for extra damage output. For defence reduction, players should use the [[dragon warhammer]] or the [[Bandos godsword]]; for extra damage output, [[dragon claws]] are the best option, followed by a [[dragon dagger]] or a [[crystal halberd]].
